  "prompt_text": "Design a database schema for a library management system with books, patrons, and loans.",
  "response_text": "**Library Management System Database Schema**\n\nThe database schema for a library management system will consist of four main entities: `Books`, `Patrons`, `Loans`, and `Authors`. The relationships between these entities will be established through foreign keys.\n\n### Tables\n\n#### Books Table\n\n| Column Name | Data Type | Description |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| `book_id` | `int` | Unique identifier for each book |\n| `title` | `varchar(255)` | Title of the book |\n| `author_id` | `int` | Foreign key referencing the `Authors` table |\n| `publisher` | `varchar(100)` | Publisher of the book |\n| `publication_date` | `date` | Date of publication |\n| `genre` | `varchar(50)` | Genre of the book (e.g., fiction, non-fiction, biography) |\n| `status` | `varchar(20)` | Status of the book (e.g., available, borrowed, lost) |\n\n#### Authors Table\n\n| Column Name | Data Type | Description |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| `author_id` | `int` | Unique identifier for each author |\n| `first_name` | `varchar(50)` | First name of the author |\n| `last_name` | `varchar(50)` | Last name of the author |\n| `date_of_birth` | `date` | Date of birth of the author |\n\n#### Patrons Table\n\n| Column Name | Data Type | Description |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| `patron_id` | `int` | Unique identifier for each patron |\n| `first_name` | `varchar(50)` | First name of the patron |\n| `last_name` | `varchar(50)` | Last name of the patron |\n| `email` | `varchar(100)` | Email address of the patron |\n| `phone_number` | `varchar(20)` | Phone number of the patron |\n| `address` | `varchar(255)` | Address of the patron |\n\n#### Loans Table\n\n| Column Name | Data Type | Description |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| `loan_id` | `int` | Unique identifier for each loan |\n| `book_id` | `int` | Foreign key referencing the `Books` table |\n| `patron_id` | `int` | Foreign key referencing the `Patrons` table |\n| `loan_date` | `date` | Date the book was loaned |\n| `due_date` | `date` | Date the book is due to be returned |\n| `return_date` | `date` | Date the book was returned (if applicable) |\n\n### Relationships\n\n- A book can have one author (one-to-one).\n- An author can write many books (one-to-many).\n- A patron can borrow many books (one-to-many).\n- A book can be borrowed by many",
